{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_016LLzK4BqAiB2uF7Y74wnFg","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The stage was run with `limit_rps: \"2\"` as override. So the limit is 2 QPS.\n\nNow the question is: with `limit-rps: 2` and the test running at 2 RPS (sleep 0.5 between requests), will we get at least 4 of 10 responses as 429?\n\nBased on my earlier analysis, with a 2 RPS limit and requests coming at exactly 2 RPS, most requests would pass through. The nginx leaky bucket algorithm would allow requests at exactly the rate limit without rejections.\n\nBut wait - let me look at the oracle to understand what it actually tests.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":924,"cache_read_input_tokens":47391,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":924},"output_tokens":28,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4ba785c4-0ca2-4cd7-a31a-144c0bb727e2","uuid":"2b445afb-9e41-4638-85c4-7b6a4fa3091b","request_id":"req_011Cc6muDQBFioDbmb3M7vXa"}
